The Canadian government will
announce plans to introduce larger, more explicit warnings on
cigarette packages, the Canadian Press reported, citing a person
it didnâ€™t identify.  The labels may increase in size to cover 75 percent of each
cigarette package, up from the current 50 percent, the news
agency said. Canadian Health Minister  Leona Aglukkaq  will
announce the new labels today at a news conference, Canadian
